    <edge id="e32" source="Cytokinin" target="TB1">
      <data key="edge_sign">negative</data>
      <data key="edge_color">#DC143C</data>
      <data key="edge_confidence">MEDIUM</data>
      <data key="edge_mechanism">CK represses TB1 via protein-level destabilisation independent of the HK4-&gt;AHP-&gt;RR21-&gt;IPA1 phosphorelay. Kept as direct edge because the canonical signalling cascade carries the opposite (positive) sign through IPA1-&gt;TB1(+1) and so cannot account for CK's tillering-promoting (TB1-repressing) effect. Consequence: hk4+trans-zeatin rescue tests will show spurious direct-arm rescue (TRAP 5 framework limitation).</data>
      <data key="edge_doi">10.1093/pcp/pcq083</data>
      <data key="edge_evidence">BAP treatment clearly suppressed FC1 expression in a concentration-dependent manner; negative control of FC1 expression by cytokinin is independent of the SL pathway.</data>
    </edge>
