      <data key="edge_sign">positive</data>
      <data key="edge_color">#228B22</data>
      <data key="edge_confidence">MEDIUM</data>
      <data key="edge_mechanism">OsBZR1 (BR-activated TF, stabilised by BZR1-D53 complex at OsTB1 promoter) net-activates OsTB1 transcription in axillary meristem. The tiller-repression phenotype upon BR treatment requires a positive BZR1-&gt;TB1 edge given the canonical TB1-&gt;Tiller_Number repression.</data>
      <data key="edge_doi">10.1016/j.molp.2019.12.005</data>
      <data key="edge_evidence">Exogenous BR stabilised the OsBZR1-D53 complex at the OsTB1 promoter and reduced tiller outgrowth. Phenotype-level evidence requires BZR1 to net-activate OsTB1 to reconcile with canonical TB1-&gt;Tiller_Number repression.</data>
    </edge>
